{"article_id":"3irfxUG58idorfCP","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"That 's what President Obama has left","depth":3},{"id":1,"text":"to prove","depth":4},{"id":2,"text":"he 's helped turn the economy around","depth":4},{"id":3,"text":"-- with just four more monthly jobs reports remaining before the November election .","depth":3},{"id":4,"text":"Those reports could determine","depth":4},{"id":5,"text":"whether he gets four more years .","depth":4},{"id":6,"text":"The last three employment snapshots","depth":8},{"id":7,"text":"released by the Labor Department","depth":8},{"id":8,"text":"have been persistently weak ,","depth":7},{"id":9,"text":"and marked a distinct slowdown from earlier in the year .","depth":6},{"id":10,"text":"In the latest report ,","depth":8},{"id":11,"text":"the department said","depth":8},{"id":12,"text":"employers added a meager 80,000 jobs in June ,","depth":8},{"id":13,"text":"leaving the unemployment rate unchanged at 8.2 percent .","depth":8},{"id":14,"text":"The number of jobs","depth":10},{"id":15,"text":"added in June","depth":10},{"id":16,"text":"was lower","depth":10},{"id":17,"text":"than expected ,","depth":10},{"id":18,"text":"and rounded out a poor second quarter for 2012 .","depth":8},{"id":19,"text":"The average number of monthly jobs","depth":11},{"id":20,"text":"created in the first quarter of the year","depth":11},{"id":21,"text":"was 226,000","depth":10},{"id":22,"text":"-- by contrast , that average in the second quarter was just 75,000","depth":9},{"id":23,"text":".","depth":8},{"id":24,"text":"With the economy typically polling as the top issue in the 2012 race ,","depth":8},{"id":25,"text":"Obama is now under heavy pressure","depth":9},{"id":26,"text":"to demonstrate a turnaround sometime between July and October .","depth":9},{"id":27,"text":"A cascade of weak jobs reports between now and then would not bode well for his chances ,","depth":8},{"id":28,"text":"though the president thus far has kept the edge over Mitt Romney in many battleground state polls .","depth":8},{"id":29,"text":"As far as Romney 's concerned ,","depth":7},{"id":30,"text":"the president has run out of time .","depth":7},{"id":31,"text":"Speaking from New Hampshire Friday ,","depth":8},{"id":32,"text":"the Republican candidate said","depth":8},{"id":33,"text":"Obama does not `` have a plan '' for the economy ,","depth":9},{"id":34,"text":"and called the latest report a `` kick in the gut . ''","depth":9},{"id":35,"text":"`` The president 's policies have clearly not been successful","depth":11},{"id":36,"text":"in re-igniting this economy , ''","depth":11},{"id":37,"text":"Romney said .","depth":10},{"id":38,"text":"`` It does n't have to be this way . ''","depth":9},{"id":39,"text":"Romney faulted the Obama administration for the country 's regulatory burden and its high corporate tax rate","depth":7},{"id":40,"text":"-- though that rate was not set by Obama ,","depth":8},{"id":41,"text":"who has actually proposed cutting it .","depth":8},{"id":42,"text":"Obama , meanwhile , was courting blue-collar voters in Ohio and Pennsylvania on his first 2012 campaign bus tour ,","depth":5},{"id":43,"text":"and took time out during a stop in Poland , Ohio ,","depth":6},{"id":44,"text":"to address the June numbers .","depth":6},{"id":45,"text":"On the upside , the president noted","depth":8},{"id":46,"text":"that over 28 months the economy has added 4.4 million payroll jobs .","depth":8},{"id":47,"text":"`` That 's a step in the right direction , ''","depth":8},{"id":48,"text":"Obama said .","depth":8},{"id":49,"text":"But the president stressed","depth":9},{"id":50,"text":"he was n't `` satisfied ''","depth":10},{"id":51,"text":"and wants to make sure","depth":11},{"id":52,"text":"middle-class families have `` basic securities . ''","depth":11},{"id":53,"text":"`` We 've got to grow the economy even faster ,","depth":10},{"id":54,"text":"and we 've got to put even more people back to work , ''","depth":10},{"id":55,"text":"Obama said .","depth":9},{"id":56,"text":"He went on to criticize Republicans","depth":9},{"id":57,"text":"for peddling a philosophy ,","depth":11},{"id":58,"text":"he said ,","depth":11},{"id":59,"text":"of less regulation and trickle-down wealth .","depth":10},{"id":60,"text":"`` I think","depth":11},{"id":61,"text":"it 's wrong , ''","depth":11},{"id":62,"text":"Obama said .","depth":10},{"id":63,"text":"`` It 's not a smart theory . ''","depth":9},{"id":64,"text":"The president took heat last month for the worst jobs report in a year","depth":7},{"id":65,"text":"-- Friday 's report was only modestly better ,","depth":7},{"id":66,"text":"opening up heated criticism from Republicans .","depth":6},{"id":67,"text":"For the U.S. economy , the only good news came in the form of incremental changes .","depth":5},{"id":68,"text":"The average work week grew to 34.5 hours from 34.4 in May ,","depth":7},{"id":69,"text":"boosting many workers ' paychecks .","depth":7},{"id":70,"text":"And average hourly wages rose 6 cents to $ 23.50 .","depth":6},{"id":71,"text":"But on a whole , none of these changes are enough","depth":7},{"id":72,"text":"to fuel an economic recovery .","depth":7},{"id":73,"text":"While professional and business services saw the best growth in June ,","depth":7},{"id":74,"text":"other industries like construction and hospitality saw almost no change in June .","depth":7},{"id":75,"text":"In the second quarter of 2012 , job growth has slowed across almost every industry .","depth":6},{"id":76,"text":"A weaker job market has made consumers less confident .","depth":8},{"id":77,"text":"They have pulled back on spending ,","depth":9},{"id":78,"text":"even though gas prices have plunged .","depth":9},{"id":79,"text":"High unemployment could shift momentum to Romney , the presumptive GOP presidential nominee .","depth":8},{"id":80,"text":"An Associated Press-GfK poll","depth":11},{"id":81,"text":"released last month","depth":11},{"id":82,"text":"found","depth":10},{"id":83,"text":"that more than half of those surveyed disapproved of Obama 's handling of the economy .","depth":9},{"id":84,"text":"Dismal June job figures could also prompt the Federal Reserve to take further action","depth":5},{"id":85,"text":"to try to boost the economy .","depth":5},{"id":86,"text":"The Fed last month downgraded its economic outlook for 2012 .","depth":6},{"id":87,"text":"It predicted growth of just 1.9 percent to 2.4 percent for the year and little change in the unemployment rate .","depth":6},{"id":88,"text":"Job gains in April and May were little changed from the department 's previous estimates .","depth":6},{"id":89,"text":"About one-third of the jobs","depth":9},{"id":90,"text":"gained in June","depth":9},{"id":91,"text":"were in temporary services .","depth":8},{"id":92,"text":"Manufacturing added 11,000 , its ninth straight month of gains .","depth":8},{"id":93,"text":"But growth in factory jobs slowed sharply in the second quarter","depth":10},{"id":94,"text":"compared to the first .","depth":10},{"id":95,"text":"Health care added 13,000 jobs","depth":10},{"id":96,"text":"and financial services gained 5,000 .","depth":11},{"id":97,"text":"Retailers , transportation firms and government cut jobs .","depth":11}],"relations":[{"parent":195,"left":103,"right":194,"relation":"organization","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":103,"left":100,"right":102,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":100,"left":0,"right":99,"relation":"purpose","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":99,"left":1,"right":2,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":102,"left":3,"right":101,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":101,"left":4,"right":5,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":194,"left":163,"right":193,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":163,"left":138,"right":162,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":138,"left":120,"right":137,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":120,"left"